# ============================================================================
# SECTION 6: HOW TO USE THIS FILE - STEP BY STEP
# ============================================================================
#
# STEP 1: GET YOUR API KEYS
# ───────────────────────────
# □ Go to https://console.anthropic.com/ and get Claude API key
# □ Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/ and get Google Vision JSON
#
# STEP 2: CREATE .env FILE
# ─────────────────────────
# □ Copy this entire file
# □ Rename to: .env (not .env.example)
# □ Save in your project root (same folder as app.py)
#
# STEP 3: FILL IN YOUR KEYS
# ──────────────────────────
# □ Replace "YOUR_ACTUAL_KEY_HERE" with your Claude API key
# □ Uncomment ONE Google Vision option and fill it in
# □ Comment out all other options
#
# STEP 4: TEST LOCALLY
# ────────────────────
# □ Open terminal in your project folder
# □ Run: streamlit run app.py
# □ Should start without asking for keys
#
# STEP 5: ADD TO .gitignore
# ──────────────────────────
# □ Make sure .env is in your .gitignore
# □ This prevents accidental commits of your secrets
# □ Use: echo ".env" >> .gitignore
#
# STEP 6: FOR VERCEL DEPLOYMENT
# ───────────────────────────────
# □ Do NOT upload .env to GitHub
# □ In Vercel dashboard, add Environment Variables:
#   - ANTHROPIC_API_KEY = sk-ant-...
#   - GOOGLE_VISION_JSON_BASE64 = (base64 string)
# □ Vercel uses these instead of .env file


# ============================================================================
# SECTION 7: SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# ============================================================================
#
# ❌ DO NOT:
#    - Share your .env file with anyone
#    - Commit .env to Git/GitHub
#    - Paste API keys in Slack or email
#    - Use someone else's API keys
#    - Leave API keys in public code
#
# ✅ DO:
#    - Keep .env in .gitignore
#    - Rotate API keys monthly
#    - Use different keys for dev/prod
#    - Monitor API usage for unusual activity
#    - Treat .env like a password
#
# IF YOUR KEY IS COMPROMISED:
# 1. Delete it immediately in the console
# 2. Generate a new one
# 3. Update .env
# 4. Update Vercel environment variables
# 5. Monitor for unusual usage


# ============================================================================
# SECTION 8: TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================
#
# ERROR: "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY not found"
# FIX:
#   1. Check spelling: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (exact case)
#   2. Verify key starts with sk-ant-
#   3. No quotes around the value
#   4. Reload terminal/app
#
# ERROR: "GOOGLE_VISION_JSON_BASE64 is invalid"
# FIX:
#   1. Verify it's real base64 (no broken encoding)
#   2. No line breaks in the middle
#   3. Complete string (didn't get truncated)
#   4. Valid JSON when decoded
#
# ERROR: "Service account JSON has wrong format"
# FIX:
#   1. Redownload JSON from Google Cloud Console
#   2. Verify it starts with {"type": "service_account"
#   3. Use the exact JSON file from Google
#
# ERROR: "File not found" (for GOOGLE_VISION_JSON_PATH)
# FIX:
#   1. Verify file exists at that path
#   2. Use absolute path, not relative
#   3. Use forward slashes on Mac/Linux, backslashes on Windows
#   4. No quotes around the path


# ============================================================================
# SECTION 9: QUICK REFERENCE
# ============================================================================
#
# VARIABLE NAME               | FORMAT                  | WHERE TO GET
# ────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┼───────────────────────
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY           | sk-ant-...              | console.anthropic.com
# GOOGLE_VISION_JSON_PATH     | /path/to/file.json      | (local file path)
# GOOGLE_VISION_JSON_BASE64   | eyJ0eXBlIjo...          | (base64 encoded JSON)
# GOOGLE_VISION_JSON          | {"type": "..."}         | (full JSON string)
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY + GOOGLE_VISION_JSON_PATH
#
# VERCEL CLOUD:
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY + GOOGLE_VISION_JSON_BASE64


